This site summarizes research and strategic frameworks led by Mark Erjavec focused on long-term U.S.–Djibouti cooperation across agriculture, infrastructure, food security, logistics, and investment systems. It includes the featured paper, “Mark Erjavec’s Early Djibouti Engagement & FAO’s Hand-in-Hand Agricultural Investment Framework,” which connects early private-sector agricultural planning in Djibouti with the FAO Hand-in-Hand initiative and outlines partnership models, value-chain development, and scalable systems design. Learn more at http://markerjavecdjibouti.com/
.
